freenet.client
Class FetchException

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Throwable
      java.lang.Exception
          freenet.client.FetchException
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class FetchException
extends Exception

Thrown when a high-level request (fetch) fails. Indicates why, whether it is worth retrying, and may give a new URI to try, the expected size of the file, its expected MIME type, and whether these are reliable. For most failure modes, except INTERNAL_ERROR there will be no stack trace, or it will be unhelpful or inaccurate.

Field Detail

mode

public final int mode
Failure mode

newURI

public final FreenetURI newURI
Try this URI instead. If we fetch a USK and there is a more recent version, for example, we will get a FetchException, but it will give a new URI to try so we can update our links, bookmarks, or convert it to an HTTP Permanent Redirect.

expectedSize

public final long expectedSize
The expected size of the data had the fetch succeeded, or -1. May not be accurate. If retrying after TOO_BIG, you need to set the temporary and final data limits to at least this big!

errorCodes

public final FailureCodeTracker errorCodes
If there are many failures, usually in a splitfile fetch, tracks the number of failures of each type.

extraMessage

public final String extraMessage
Extra information about the failure.
